<subSubSection lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,2010,2037]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1437,151,1221]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,2010,2036]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Epandrial phragma prominent (wider than epandrial anteroventral corner), somewhat shell-shaped expansion on antero-subapical margin (ch.33-1; 
<figureCitation box="[704,809,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-299@14.[151,1435,885,1672]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Characters 30‒39 on the periphallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, anterior view), C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, ventral view; E, surstylus) and C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (F, oblique lateral view; G, ventral view; H, surstylus). Abbreviations: cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766422/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
). Surstyli absent (ch.34-2; 
<figureCitation box="[1119,1224,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-299@14.[151,1435,885,1672]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Characters 30‒39 on the periphallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, anterior view), C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, ventral view; E, surstylus) and C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (F, oblique lateral view; G, ventral view; H, surstylus). Abbreviations: cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766422/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
). Lateral pieces of subepandrial sclerite less sclerotized, small, somewhat triangular plate-like (ch.37-1; 
<figureCitation box="[1145,1253,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-299@14.[151,1435,885,1672]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Characters 30‒39 on the periphallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, anterior view), C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, ventral view; E, surstylus) and C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (F, oblique lateral view; G, ventral view; H, surstylus). Abbreviations: cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766422/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
). Cercus nearly entirely oval (ch.38-1; 
<figureCitation box="[409,512,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-299@14.[151,1435,885,1672]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Characters 30‒39 on the periphallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, anterior view), C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, ventral view; E, surstylus) and C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (F, oblique lateral view; G, ventral view; H, surstylus). Abbreviations: cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766422/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
). Phallal sheath prominently projected anterodorsad at dorsobasal corner in lateral view (ch.41-2; 
<figureCitation box="[321,424,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1315,1339]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetId="figure-43@16.[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Characters 40‒47 on the phallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, ventral view; C, hypandrium and gonocoxites, oblique lateral view), C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (D, lateral view; E, ventral view), C. sabahana sp. nov. (F, lateral view; G, ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (H, lateral view; I, ventral view).Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; goncx, gonocoxite; hypd, hypandrium; phap, phallapodeme; ph sh, phallal sheath. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766424/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,425,294,321]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Shared characters.</emphasis>
Supracervical setae distally more or less curved, longer than inner occipital setae (ch.1-0; 
<figureCitation box="[151,239,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1541,1565]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1517]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[151,1435,181,1517]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Characters 1‒4 on the head of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A‒D) and C. cristata de Meijere (E‒H). A, E, Caudal view; B, F, dorsal view; C, G, frontal view; D, H, right eye (frontal view). Abbreviations: ar, arista; a rc orb s, anterior reclinate orbital seta; i ocp s, inner occipital setae; pc orb s, proclinate orbital seta; spc s, supracervical setae. Character states are indicated in the form of ‘character No.-state code’. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766408/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Additional, interfrontal setulae on fronto-orbital plate absent (ch.2-1; 
<figureCitation box="[1031,1117,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1541,1565]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1517]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[151,1435,181,1517]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Characters 1‒4 on the head of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A‒D) and C. cristata de Meijere (E‒H). A, E, Caudal view; B, F, dorsal view; C, G, frontal view; D, H, right eye (frontal view). Abbreviations: ar, arista; a rc orb s, anterior reclinate orbital seta; i ocp s, inner occipital setae; pc orb s, proclinate orbital seta; spc s, supracervical setae. Character states are indicated in the form of ‘character No.-state code’. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766408/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Distance between antennal sockets wider than half of socket width (ch.4-0; 
<figureCitation box="[702,790,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1541,1565]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1517]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[151,1435,181,1517]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Characters 1‒4 on the head of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A‒D) and C. cristata de Meijere (E‒H). A, E, Caudal view; B, F, dorsal view; C, G, frontal view; D, H, right eye (frontal view). Abbreviations: ar, arista; a rc orb s, anterior reclinate orbital seta; i ocp s, inner occipital setae; pc orb s, proclinate orbital seta; spc s, supracervical setae. Character states are indicated in the form of ‘character No.-state code’. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766408/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). Cibarial, medial sensilla in parallel rows narrower than sensilla campaniformia (ch.5-2); posterior sensilla present (ch.6-0). Anterior dorsocentral setae situated behind transverse suture (ch.7-0; 
<figureCitation box="[445,536,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,920,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-75@10.[151,1435,919,1851]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Characters 7‒11 on the thorax (A‒D, dorsal view; E‒G, lateral view) of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, E), C. grandis sp. nov. (B), C. cristata de Meijere (C, F), C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada) (D) and C. ecornuta sp. nov. (G). Abbreviations: a dc s, anterior dorsocentral setae; ap sctl s, apical scutellar seta; b sctl s, basal scutellar seta; p kepst s, posterior katepisternal seta; pprn s, postpronotal seta; trn sut, transverse suture. Scale bars: 0.5 mm in A‒D, 0.1 mm in E‒G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766412/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Additional dorsocentral setae on presutural area absent (
<figureCitation box="[1192,1283,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,920,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-75@10.[151,1435,919,1851]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Characters 7‒11 on the thorax (A‒D, dorsal view; E‒G, lateral view) of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, E), C. grandis sp. nov. (B), C. cristata de Meijere (C, F), C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada) (D) and C. ecornuta sp. nov. (G). Abbreviations: a dc s, anterior dorsocentral setae; ap sctl s, apical scutellar seta; b sctl s, basal scutellar seta; p kepst s, posterior katepisternal seta; pprn s, postpronotal seta; trn sut, transverse suture. Scale bars: 0.5 mm in A‒D, 0.1 mm in E‒G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766412/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Prescutellar acrostichal setae absent (ch.8-1; 
<figureCitation box="[514,603,474,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,920,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-75@10.[151,1435,919,1851]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Characters 7‒11 on the thorax (A‒D, dorsal view; E‒G, lateral view) of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, E), C. grandis sp. nov. (B), C. cristata de Meijere (C, F), C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada) (D) and C. ecornuta sp. nov. (G). Abbreviations: a dc s, anterior dorsocentral setae; ap sctl s, apical scutellar seta; b sctl s, basal scutellar seta; p kepst s, posterior katepisternal seta; pprn s, postpronotal seta; trn sut, transverse suture. Scale bars: 0.5 mm in A‒D, 0.1 mm in E‒G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766412/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Acrostichal setulae in 4 rows (ch.9-0; 
<figureCitation box="[1046,1135,474,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,920,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-75@10.[151,1435,919,1851]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Characters 7‒11 on the thorax (A‒D, dorsal view; E‒G, lateral view) of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, E), C. grandis sp. nov. (B), C. cristata de Meijere (C, F), C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada) (D) and C. ecornuta sp. nov. (G). Abbreviations: a dc s, anterior dorsocentral setae; ap sctl s, apical scutellar seta; b sctl s, basal scutellar seta; p kepst s, posterior katepisternal seta; pprn s, postpronotal seta; trn sut, transverse suture. Scale bars: 0.5 mm in A‒D, 0.1 mm in E‒G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766412/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Katepisternal setae large; posterior one as long as or longer than longest, postpronotal seta (ch.10-0; 
<figureCitation box="[1020,1108,510,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,920,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-75@10.[151,1435,919,1851]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Characters 7‒11 on the thorax (A‒D, dorsal view; E‒G, lateral view) of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, E), C. grandis sp. nov. (B), C. cristata de Meijere (C, F), C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada) (D) and C. ecornuta sp. nov. (G). Abbreviations: a dc s, anterior dorsocentral setae; ap sctl s, apical scutellar seta; b sctl s, basal scutellar seta; p kepst s, posterior katepisternal seta; pprn s, postpronotal seta; trn sut, transverse suture. Scale bars: 0.5 mm in A‒D, 0.1 mm in E‒G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766412/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
). Basal scutellar setae short; posterior tip not reaching to half of apical scutellar setae (ch.11-0; 
<figureCitation box="[887,976,546,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,920,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-75@10.[151,1435,919,1851]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Characters 7‒11 on the thorax (A‒D, dorsal view; E‒G, lateral view) of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, E), C. grandis sp. nov. (B), C. cristata de Meijere (C, F), C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada) (D) and C. ecornuta sp. nov. (G). Abbreviations: a dc s, anterior dorsocentral setae; ap sctl s, apical scutellar seta; b sctl s, basal scutellar seta; p kepst s, posterior katepisternal seta; pprn s, postpronotal seta; trn sut, transverse suture. Scale bars: 0.5 mm in A‒D, 0.1 mm in E‒G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766412/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Apical scutellar setae nearly equidistant from each other and from basal scutellar seta (
<figureCitation box="[675,766,582,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,920,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-75@10.[151,1435,919,1851]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Characters 7‒11 on the thorax (A‒D, dorsal view; E‒G, lateral view) of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, E), C. grandis sp. nov. (B), C. cristata de Meijere (C, F), C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada) (D) and C. ecornuta sp. nov. (G). Abbreviations: a dc s, anterior dorsocentral setae; ap sctl s, apical scutellar seta; b sctl s, basal scutellar seta; p kepst s, posterior katepisternal seta; pprn s, postpronotal seta; trn sut, transverse suture. Scale bars: 0.5 mm in A‒D, 0.1 mm in E‒G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766412/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Apically blunt, heavy, peg-like costal setae in middle row interspersed with weak, trichoid ones (ch.12-1; 
<figureCitation box="[700,790,619,646]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1951,1975]" captionTargetBox="[286,1299,181,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[286,1300,181,1927]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Character 12 of costal setae on the wing (anterodistal portion) of Colocasiomyia xenalocasiae (Okada) (A), C. colocasiae (Duda) (B) and C. cristata de Meijere (C). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766414/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
). Fore tarsomere I with patch covered with only minute pubescence on anterodorsal portion (ch.13-0; 
<figureCitation box="[674,765,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,903,927]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,878]" captionTargetId="figure-22@12.[151,1435,181,879]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Characters 13‒15 on the fore (A, B, distal portion of tibia and tarsus) and mid (C, D, ditto) legs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, C) and C. cristata de Meijere (B, D). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766416" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766416/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
). Mid tibia with 2 or more apical setae (ch.15-0; 
<figureCitation box="[1334,1423,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,903,927]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,878]" captionTargetId="figure-22@12.[151,1435,181,879]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Characters 13‒15 on the fore (A, B, distal portion of tibia and tarsus) and mid (C, D, ditto) legs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, C) and C. cristata de Meijere (B, D). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766416" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766416/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
). Male abdominal sternites IV and V and female sternites III–VI longer than wide (ch.17–22-1; 
<figureCitation box="[1239,1357,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,987,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-64@12.[151,1435,987,1918]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Characters 16‒22 on the male (A, C) and female (B, D) abdominal sternites (s) of Colocasiomyia gigantea (Okada) (A, B) and C. colocasiae (Duda) (C, D). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766418" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766418/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 8C,D</figureCitation>
). Male abdominal sternite VI not pubescent at least partly (ch.23-0; 
<figureCitation box="[864,990,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male abdominal sternite VIs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (B in anteroventral view, C in lateral view), C. stamenicola (Carson &amp; Okada) (D in anterior view) and all species of the C. cristata subgroup (A in ventral view, E‒R in anterior view): A, C. ecornuta sp. nov.; E, C. grandis sp. nov.; F, C. vieti sp. nov.; G, C. cristata de Meijere; H, C. matthewsi sp. nov.; I, C. sulawesiana Okada &amp; Yafuso; J, C. kinabaluana sp. nov.; K, C. kotana sp. nov.; L, C. sabahana sp. nov.; M, C. sarawakana sp. nov.; N, C. pistilicola (Carson &amp; Okada); O, C. xenalocasiae (Okada); P, C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada); Q, C. sumatrana sp. nov.; and R, C. leucocasiae sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766420/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 9B–D</figureCitation>
), with single process longer than 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.05 mm</quantity>
and not bearing prominent seta on apex but small setae on submedial to distal portion (ch.24-2, 25–27-0; 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male abdominal sternite VIs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (B in anteroventral view, C in lateral view), C. stamenicola (Carson &amp; Okada) (D in anterior view) and all species of the C. cristata subgroup (A in ventral view, E‒R in anterior view): A, C. ecornuta sp. nov.; E, C. grandis sp. nov.; F, C. vieti sp. nov.; G, C. cristata de Meijere; H, C. matthewsi sp. nov.; I, C. sulawesiana Okada &amp; Yafuso; J, C. kinabaluana sp. nov.; K, C. kotana sp. nov.; L, C. sabahana sp. nov.; M, C. sarawakana sp. nov.; N, C. pistilicola (Carson &amp; Okada); O, C. xenalocasiae (Okada); P, C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada); Q, C. sumatrana sp. nov.; and R, C. leucocasiae sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766420/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 9B–D</figureCitation>
). Epandrium roundish on posteroventral margin (ch.30-1), with seta as long as width of epandrium and short setae as thick as cercal setae on posteroventral portion (ch.31,32-0; 
<figureCitation box="[899,1002,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-299@14.[151,1435,885,1672]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Characters 30‒39 on the periphallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, anterior view), C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, ventral view; E, surstylus) and C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (F, oblique lateral view; G, ventral view; H, surstylus). Abbreviations: cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766422/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
). Median piece of subepandrial sclerite broad, somewhat quadrate plate (ch.36-0; 
<figureCitation box="[635,767,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-299@14.[151,1435,885,1672]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Characters 30‒39 on the periphallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, anterior view), C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, ventral view; E, surstylus) and C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (F, oblique lateral view; G, ventral view; H, surstylus). Abbreviations: cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766422/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 10A,B</figureCitation>
). Cercus wider than 1/2 cercal length (ch.39-1; 
<figureCitation box="[1318,1424,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-299@14.[151,1435,885,1672]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Characters 30‒39 on the periphallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, anterior view), C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, ventral view; E, surstylus) and C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (F, oblique lateral view; G, ventral view; H, surstylus). Abbreviations: cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766422/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
). Phallal sheath nearly straight, apically vertically bilobed, as thick as wide, without pubescence (ch.40-0, 42–44-1; 
<figureCitation box="[151,281,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1315,1339]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetId="figure-43@16.[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Characters 40‒47 on the phallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, ventral view; C, hypandrium and gonocoxites, oblique lateral view), C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (D, lateral view; E, ventral view), C. sabahana sp. nov. (F, lateral view; G, ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (H, lateral view; I, ventral view).Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; goncx, gonocoxite; hypd, hypandrium; phap, phallapodeme; ph sh, phallal sheath. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766424/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 11A,B</figureCitation>
). Phallapodeme more or less sclerotized, slightly oblique to axis of phallal sheath, longer than 1/2 of phallal sheath (ch.45-1, ch.46,47-0; 
<figureCitation box="[551,678,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1315,1339]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetId="figure-43@16.[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Characters 40‒47 on the phallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, ventral view; C, hypandrium and gonocoxites, oblique lateral view), C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (D, lateral view; E, ventral view), C. sabahana sp. nov. (F, lateral view; G, ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (H, lateral view; I, ventral view).Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; goncx, gonocoxite; hypd, hypandrium; phap, phallapodeme; ph sh, phallal sheath. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766424/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 11A,B</figureCitation>
). Epiproct and hypoproct pubescent (ch.48-0; 
<figureCitation box="[1190,1319,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[151,250,762,786]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,182,734]" captionTargetId="figure-18@17.[151,1435,181,737]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Characters 48‒51 on the female terminalia of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, hypoproct in ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, hypoproct in ventral view). Abbreviations: epiprct, epiproct; hyprct, hypoproct; ov, oviscapt; t-VIII, tergite VIII. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766426/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 12A,B</figureCitation>
). Oviscapt not longer than phallus (apodeme + sheath), with ovisensilla on portion occupying 1/2 or more in length of oviscapt; distal portion differentiated into more or less narrow process from basal, broad portion with dense, fine wrinkles (ch. 49–51-0; 
<figureCitation box="[309,412,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[151,250,762,786]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,182,734]" captionTargetId="figure-18@17.[151,1435,181,737]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Characters 48‒51 on the female terminalia of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, hypoproct in ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, hypoproct in ventral view). Abbreviations: epiprct, epiproct; hyprct, hypoproct; ov, oviscapt; t-VIII, tergite VIII. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766426/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
