<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,402,1122,1149]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Included species.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Duda" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[409,704,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Colocasiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colocasiae">
<emphasis box="[409,704,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Colocasiomyia colocasiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Okada" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[718,858,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Colocasiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alocasiae">
<emphasis box="[718,858,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. alocasiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Okada" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[873,1012,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Colocasiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iskandari">
<emphasis box="[873,1012,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. iskandari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1026,1182,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Colocasiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steudnerae">
<emphasis box="[1026,1182,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. steudnerae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Carson &amp; Okada" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[1237,1405,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Colocasiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stamenicola">
<emphasis box="[1237,1256,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1270,1405,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">stamenicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A total of 14 putatively new species probably belong to this subgroup (
<bibRefCitation author="Fartyal, R. S. &amp; Gao, J. J. &amp; Toda, M. J. &amp; Hu, Y. G. &amp; Takano, K. T. &amp; Suwito, A. &amp; Katoh, T. &amp; Takigahira, T. &amp; Yin, J. T." box="[909,1116,1159,1185]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="763 - 782" refId="ref32284" refString="Fartyal, R. S., Gao, J. J., Toda, M. J., Hu, Y. G., Takano, K. T., Suwito, A., Katoh, T., Takigahira, T. &amp; Yin, J. T. (2013) Colocasiomyia (Diptera: Drosophilidae) revised phylogenetically, with a new species group having peculiar lifecycles on monsteroid (Araceae) host plants. Systematic Entomology, 38, 763 - 782. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12027" type="journal article" year="2013">
Fartyal 
<emphasis box="[996,1044,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
; Toda unpublished data; 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="19.[151,250,943,967]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,182,919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@19.[151,1436,181,919]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 14. Geographical distributions of all species of the Colocasiomyia cristata group." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766432/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). The species-status determination and description of them will be done elsewhere.
</paragraph>
